<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Fragment from the front of a <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> garland <rs type="objectType">sarcophagus</rs> <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.75</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.42</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.13</measure>; for decription see <bibl>Isik 170</bibl>
</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face within a tabella (die, <measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.26</measure>   × <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.22</measure>), impinging on the right-hand moulding; the surface is badly worn.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.015</measure>; moderate quality, poorly aligned, but wear has obscured detail.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>Perhaps 
<date notBefore="0201" notAfter="0250" exact="none" cert="low"> first half of the third century</date>
 (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">nomenclature</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w>  <w lemma="σορός">σορός</w>  <w lemma="εἰμί">ἐστιν</w>  <lb n="2"/><persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Μᾶρκος">Μάρκ<unclear reason="damage">ου</unclear></name>  <name reg="Αὐρήλιος"><unclear reason="damage">Αὐ</unclear>ρηλι<lb n="3" type="worddiv"/>ου</name>  <name reg="Ἀντίοχος">Ἀντιόχου</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <lb n="4"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Εἰσαγόρας"><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">εισα</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" extent="8" unit="character" dim="right"/>  </name></persName></persName><lb n="5"/><orig n="unresolved">ω</orig>  <gap reason="lost" extent="1" unit="character"/>  <orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">λ</unclear></orig>  <gap reason="lost" extent="9" unit="character" dim="right"/>  <lb n="5a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line" dim="bottom"/>  </ab>
</div>
<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>The sarcophagus belongs to Marcus Aurelius Antiochus the son of Eis[- ... <note>(perhaps Eisagoras)</note></p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>

<p>Probably one of the shorter type texts; but the owner, although apparently possessing only the sarcophagus, gave his Roman name in full and cited at least his father's name in the Greek manner, suggesting a date not too long after the Edict of Caracalla in A.D. 212.</p></div>
